# 🚀 Nexus Repository Manager on Kubernetes (Helm Deployment)

## 📌 Overview

This project demonstrates how to deploy **Sonatype Nexus Repository Manager** on Kubernetes using Helm. Nexus acts as a central artifact repository for storing and managing build artifacts such as Docker images, Maven dependencies, and more.

---

## 🧰 Tech Stack

* Kubernetes (EKS / Minikube / K8s Cluster)
* Helm (v3+)
* Nexus Repository Manager (Docker Image)
* Persistent Volume (PVC)
* NodePort Service

---

